message.content: Yes, the authors describe the limitations of their work as they mention that their techniques rely on the specific structure of two-sample U-statistics of degree 2 and extending these to more general U-statistics of higher degrees is an important question for future work. They also discuss that achieving minimax optimal power using a sub-quadratic time test statistic is an open question, and they suggest a potential approach involving kernel approximated by random Fourier features. They leave this question for future work.

Additionally, they pose a question regarding whether it is possible to achieve minimax optimal power using a sub-quadratic time test statistic, leaving this important question for future work.
